The paper deals with lower bounds for circuits computing connectivity in graphs, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The techniques used involve circuit complexity, graph theory, and information theory, which are all central topics in theoretical computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
